    content: "## The 60-Second Version\n\n**THE PALS — VERBAL PITCH**\n\n```\n\"At Palmer House, every project gets assigned a **Pal**. A Pal isn't a person — it's a **mode**. It's how we name what kind of work we're doing for you, so the whole team knows what 'good' looks like.\n\nThere are four Pals:\n\n→ **Visibility Pal** — content that makes you findable. SEO video, top-of-funnel.\n→ **YouTube Pal** — long-form that builds an audience. Episodic, character-driven.\n→ **Commercial Pal** — paid spots that move product. Tight, persuasive, conversion-focused.\n→ **Systems Pal** — internal video. Training, SOPs, async comms.\n\nWhen you sign with us, I'll tell you exactly which Pal we're working in — and that decides everything from the script style to the edit pace to what we benchmark against. It keeps us honest.\"\n```\n\n## Why It Works (the why, for internal use)\n\nThe Pal system solves three problems at once:\n\n- Clients get a frame for what they're buying — instead of \"a video,\" they're buying a kind of video.\n- The team gets a shared vocabulary — \"this needs more Kareem energy\" is faster than a paragraph of notes.\n- The brand gets a moat — nobody else talks about video this way.\n\n## Cross-Pal Projects\n\nSometimes a project is two Pals. Be explicit:\n\n> \"This one is mostly YouTube Pal with a Commercial Pal cutdown at the end — so we'll script it for retention but cut a 30-second paid version from the same shoot.\"",
