    inputsNeeded: "• Google Docs (master)  • Frame.io for read-along  • Notion linked to project",
    content: "## The Two-Column Format\n\n**Left column:** what is heard (VO, dialogue, music cue). **Right column:** what is seen (shot, B-roll, text overlay). Always paired, always parallel.\n\n**SCRIPT — SAMPLE ROW**\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────┐\n│ AUDIO                       │ VIDEO                       │\n├─────────────────────────────┼─────────────────────────────┤\n│ **[VO — JEVOY]**             │ **[WIDE]** Jevoy walks         │\n│ \"I started this company     │ across the studio, late     │\n│ because nobody was making   │ afternoon light through     │\n│ video the way I wanted to   │ the window. Steady cam.     │\n│ watch it.\"                  │                             │\n│                             │ **[B-ROLL]** Hands on the     │\n│ **[MUSIC IN — sage_reel.mp3]** │ camera, lens cap pulled.   │\n│                             │                             │\n│ Duration: 0:08              │ Duration: 0:08              │\n└─────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## The 7 Format Rules\n\n1. Timestamp every block. No \"we'll figure out length in the edit.\"\n2. Slug lines in ALL CAPS (WIDE, CU, B-ROLL, MUSIC IN).\n3. Bold all speakers. [VO — JEVOY], [DIALOGUE — CLIENT].\n4. Italics for non-verbal direction. (beat), (laughing).\n5. Music cues are inline, named. No \"TBD track.\"\n6. Read every script out loud before sending. Time it.\n7. Final scripts get a version number — v1, v1.1, FINAL. Never \"FINAL_FINAL.\"\n\n## Script Review Checklist\n\n- [ ] First 5 seconds earn the next 15\n- [ ] One idea per scene\n- [ ] No line is longer than a single breath\n- [ ] Every \"tell\" has a paired \"show\"\n- [ ] The end ties back to the open\n- [ ] Read out loud — does it sound like a human?",
