    purpose: "The 7 / 30 / 90 day rhythm. Three short messages. Zero sales pressure.",
    ownerRole: "owner",
    whenToUse: "**THE WHY** — A 7/30/90 cadence keeps us present without becoming spam. It also catches dissatisfaction early — before it becomes a refund request or a bad referral.",
    trigger: "",
    inputsNeeded: "",
    content: "## Day 7 — \"How's it landing?\"\n\n**DAY 7 — TEXT OR EMAIL**\n\n```\nHey [Name] — quick check-in. You've had the film for a week. How's it landing? Anyone reach out? Anything you'd change knowing what you know now? No agenda — just want to hear how it's going. 🎬\n```\n\n## Day 30 — \"The reflection\"\n\n**DAY 30 — EMAIL**\n\n```\nHey [Name],\n\nA month in — wanted to check in properly.\n\nThree quick questions, answer however brief feels right:\n\n1. What's working? (What are you most glad we made?)\n2. What's not landing the way you hoped?\n3. If you could go back and add or change one thing, what would it be?\n\nYour answers help me get better. And they help me think about what we'd do **next** if there's a next.\n\n— Jevoy\n```\n\n## Day 90 — \"The next move\"\n\n**DAY 90 — EMAIL OR CALL**\n\n```\nHey [Name],\n\n90 days since we shipped. Long enough to know what worked.\n\nA few things I've been thinking about for you specifically:\n\n→ [Specific observation from their data or what they shared]\n→ [What you'd do next, given that]\n\nWant to grab 20 minutes next week to talk through what's next? No proposal, no pressure — just thinking out loud together.\n\n— Jevoy\n```",
