    content: "## The 3-2-1 Standard\n\n**3 copies. 2 different media. 1 offsite.** Every project, every time.\n\n- Copy 1 (working): Editor's local SSD or NAS\n- Copy 2 (mirror): Studio RAID\n- Copy 3 (offsite): Backblaze B2 (cloud) — runs nightly\n\n## The Schedule\n\n| Frequency | What | Where |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **Real-time** | Project files (NLE saves) | Editor SSD ↔ NAS sync |\n| **Nightly 11pm** | All active project folders | NAS → Backblaze |\n| **Weekly Fri 6pm** | Full team Drive snapshot | Backblaze versioning |\n| **On wrap** | Project SSD duplicated | Cold storage drive (locked) |\n| **12-month archive** | Move to /10_ARCHIVE/ | Cold storage + cloud |\n\n## Recovery Test (quarterly)\n\nEvery quarter, pull a random project from cold storage and verify:\n\n- [ ] Cold drive boots\n- [ ] All folders intact\n- [ ] Open the .prproj — does it relink?\n- [ ] Backblaze copy matches\n\nLog result in /09_INTERNAL/Backup_Tests/.\n\n> **THE RED LINE** — No project gets wrapped until all 3 copies are confirmed. \"I'll back it up tomorrow\" is how studios lose footage. Tomorrow is when the drive dies.",
